Input: root = [1, 2, 3, 4, N, 10, 5, N, N, N, N, 6, 7]

Output: 3
Explanation: The longest path from the root(node 1) to a leaf node 6 with 3 edges. have to count longest number of edges//
IMP*** In counting edges return -1 
  IMP** In counting nodes return 0

class Solution {
 
    public int height(Node root) {
    
    
        if(root==null){
            return -1;
        }
        int left=height(root.left);
        int right=height(root.right);
        return Math.max(left,right)+1;
        
    }
}
